This feature begain its life as the DigitalOcean Poster Service (do_poster).  It's now being referred to by its other name, Skolr.

To build, clone the repo, and run the dependencies.make file using Drush Make.

1. clone the repo
2. drush make a drupal installation with all the necessary modules
2. create a db and user if setting up the site for the first time
3. drush si to setup a db and settings.php file
4. enable the skolr module (legacy name: do_poster)

Example:

$ git clone git://github.com/ezwart/skolr.git
$ drush make skolr/dependencies.make drupal
$ mysql -u root -p

mysql> CREATE DATABASE skolr;
mysql> GRANT ALL ON skolr.* TO skolr@localhost IDENTIFIED BY 'fakepwd';
mysql> exit

$ cd drupal
$ drush si --db-url="mysql://skolr:fakepwd@localhost/skolr" --site-name="Skolr"
$ drush en do_poster -y

